I'm not entirely sure what you are trying to do but you can use the modulus function, this code would let you write seperate HTML for 6 different
```{% for content in contents %}
	{% if loop.index % 6 == 1 %}
		//HTML for post 1,7,etc
	{% elif loop.index % 6 == 2 %}
		//HTML for post 2,8,etc
	{% elif loop.index % 6 == 3 %}
		//HTML 
	{% elif loop.index % 6 == 4 %}
		//HTML 
	{% elif loop.index % 6 == 5 %}
		//HTML 
	{% if loop.index % 6 == 0 %}
		//HTML for post 6,12,etc
	{% endif %}
{% endfor %}```

sorry like position of the post, 1,2,3 etc

e.g. if you have six posts per page and want post 1 and 4 to have some code and all the others to have some other code you can do
```{% if loop.index == 1 || loop.index ==4 %}
//Render this HTML
{% else %}
//Redner this HTML
{% endif %}```

